[Luke 4:10](../../../bib/kjv/luk004.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">luk 4:10</span></span>

angels

(See Scofield) - ([Heb 1:4](../../../bib/kjv/heb001.htm#004).md).

to keep

After Satan's failure to tempt the Lord away from the Word, he seeks to
tempt Him by it. He however misquotes by the omission of "in all thy
ways" ([Psa 91:11](../../../bib/kjv/psa091.htm#011).md). The Lord's "ways"
were those marked out for Him in perfect dependence upon His Father's
will.

Compare ([Heb 10:7](../../../bib/kjv/heb010.htm#007).md); ([Heb
10:9](../../../bib/kjv/heb010.htm#009).md).

